'''Siphesihle Qhamani 'Pitsa' Punguzwa''' (born 21 May 1993 in [[Butterworth, Eastern Cape|Butterworth]]) is a South African [[rugby union]] player for the {{Rut Border Bulldogs}} in the [[Currie Cup]] and in the [[Rugby Challenge (South Africa)|Rugby Challenge]].<ref name="SARU Player Profile Siphesihle Punguzwa">{{SA Rugby Player Profile | id=49517 | name=Siphesihle Punguzwa | date=29 May 2016}}</ref> His regular position is flanker.

==Career==

===Youth===

Punguzwa represented his home province of Border at both the 2009 Under-16 Grant Khomo Week and the 2011 Under-18 [[Craven Week]] tournaments. He then moved to [[Port Elizabeth]] to join the {{Rut Eastern Province Kings}}. He played in all nine matches of the {{Rut Eastern Province U21}} side's [[2013 Under-21 Provincial Championship]] Division B campaign, making five starts and four substitute appearances and scoring eight tries, the joint-highest by a forward in the competition.<ref name="SA Rugby Try Scorers – 2013 Absa Under 21 Competition">{{SA Rugby Try Scorers | id=1434 | comp=2013 Absa Under 21 Competition | date=5 May 2016}}</ref> His try-scoring feats included braces against {{Rut SWD U21}}<ref name="EP Kings 76-16 SWD">{{SA Rugby Match Centre | id=110984 | homeid=15334 | awayid=15304 | leagueid=1434 | hometeam=EP Kings | homescore=76 | awayscore=16 | awayteam=SWD | matchdate=6 September 2013 | date=6 December 2016}}</ref> and {{Rut Falcons U21}}.<ref name="EP Kings 87-17 Valke">{{SA Rugby Match Centre | id=111064 | homeid=15334 | awayid=15354 | leagueid=1434 | hometeam=EP Kings | homescore=87 | awayscore=17 | awayteam=Valke | matchdate=20 September 2013 | date=6 December 2016}}</ref> He also played in their promotion/relegation play-off match against former side {{Rut Border U21}}, but, despite scoring yet another try in the match, could not help {{Rut Eastern Province U21}} gain promotion to Division A.<ref name="Border 23-21 EP Kings">{{SA Rugby Match Centre | id=114954 | homeid=16374 | awayid=16384 | leagueid=1614 | hometeam=Border | homescore=23 | awayscore=21 | awayteam=EP Kings | matchdate=19 October 2013 | date=6 December 2016}}</ref>

===Senior career===

He was included in the {{Rut Eastern Province Kings}} for the first time for the [[2014 Vodacom Cup]] competition<ref name="SA Rugby Squad – Eastern Province Kings : 2014 Vodacom Cup">{{SA Rugby Squad | teamid=17554 | team=Eastern Province Kings | compid=1734 | comp=2014 Vodacom Cup | accessdate=3 June 2016}}</ref> and made his senior debut by coming on as a substitute in their 17–10 opening day defeat to [[Kenya]]n side {{Rut Simba XV}}.<ref name="Tusker Simba XV 17-10 Eastern Province Kings">{{SA Rugby Match Centre | id=118814 | homeid=17574 | awayid=17554 | leagueid=1734 | hometeam=Tusker Simba XV | homescore=17 | awayscore=10 | awayteam=Eastern Province Kings | matchdate=8 March 2014 | date=6 December 2016}}</ref> Three more substitute appearances followed – with Punguzwa scoring his first senior try for the Kings in their 28–21 victory over {{Rut Boland Cavaliers}}<ref name="Eastern Province Kings 28-21 Regent Boland Cavaliers">{{SA Rugby Match Centre | id=118164 | homeid=17554 | awayid=17534 | leagueid=1734 | hometeam=Eastern Province Kings | homescore=28 | awayscore=21 | awayteam=Regent Boland Cavaliers | matchdate=11 April 2014 | date=6 December 2016}}</ref> – before he was named in the starting line-up for the first time for their match against the {{Rut Sharks XV}} in [[Durban]].

